{"cursor":"31162","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Hard water' is water that has high mineral content (in contrast with\n\"soft water\").\n\nHard drinking water is generally not harmful to one's health, World Health Organization\n[http://www.who.int/water_sanitation_health/dwq/chemicals/en/hardness.pdf\nHardness in Drinking-Water], 2003 but can pose serious problems in\nindustrial settings, where water hardness is monitored to avoid costly\nbreakdowns in boilers, cooling towers, and other equipment that handles water.\nIn domestic settings, hard water is often indicated by a lack of suds formation\nwhen soap is agitated in water. Wherever water hardness is a concern, water\nsoftening is commonly used to reduce hard water's adverse effects.\n","linknr":523,"url":"Hard_water","recorded":1362372255,"links":65,"instances":["measure","element","chemist","chemistry","chemistry","chemistry","mineral"],"pdf":["http://www.who.int/water_sanitation_health/dwq/chemicals/en/hardness.pdf","http://www.wrc.org.za/Knowledge%20Hub%20Documents/Water%20SA%20Journals/Manuscripts/1998/01/WaterSA_1998_01_jan98_p77.pdf","http://www.wrc.org.za/Knowledge%20Hub%20Documents/Water%20SA%20Journals/Manuscripts/1998/01/WaterSA_1998_01_jan98_p77.pdf","http://www.aquasafecanada.com/mirror/hardness/hardness.pdf","http://www.melbournewater.com.au/content/library/publications/reports/compliance_reports/public_health_compliance_quarter_1_(july-september_2006).pdf","http://www.watercorporation.com.au/_files/DWQ_AR_0506_withAppB.pdf","http://www.nt.gov.au/powerwater/docs/water_quality/2005/Water%20Quality.pdf","http://www.gvrd.bc.ca/sewerage/pdf/washsmart.pdf","http://www.aquasafecanada.com/mirror/water_report_2006/Water_Report_2006.pdf","http://www.aquasafecanada.com/mirror/water_report_2006/Water_Report_2006.pdf","http://www.regionofwaterloo.ca/en/aboutTheEnvironment/resources/WaterSoftenerReportApril2011.pdf","http://www.regionofwaterloo.ca/en/aboutTheEnvironment/resources/Wate